<br />
Nah. I do. I know a lot of others that do. And there are a shitpile of people who are new to mmorpgs who have never even tried the EQ way and might like it.<br />
<br />
Back when the gamespace of mmorpg were about .5 mill, yeah. Asking for those numbers, not too smart.<br />
<br />
Once WoW added about 7 million, in addition to making mmorpgs mainstream... Having high optimistic hopes of 1 million subs is not out of line.<br />
<br />
I am fairly certain, as most of us are, that Vanguard will never reach WoWs numbers. The only mmorpg in my mind in development or that I can think of being made even that could do that, would be LOTR. But that won't either now.<br />
But saying that Vanguard can eventually reach 500k+ up to a million people, that's not completely out of the realm of possability anymore.<br />
<br />
I don't think it'll happen, but I don't think it could never happen.... if that made sense.<br />
It won't be the game at the top, but if Vanguard is released and made the way they have intended, then the game will be a success for what they are going for, and Vanguard will sit comfortably amongst the top of the mmorpgs.
                  
