		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_917198">
                  
                  It's not 1999, and I just don't see 1 million gamers putting up with that shit anymore.<br />
<br />
Let me tell you what made EQ a hit.<br />
<br />
A PK switch.<br />
<br />
Now if that was Brad's idea, then give the man a medal, because it means he's only slightly less out of touch than Raph Koster.<br />
<br />
EQ became a hit, because players were tired of getting gang banged in UO, and SOE made the mistake of thinking their shit didn't stink, when all they did was publish the nearest thing to D+D with a pk switch that anyone had ever seen.<br />
<br />
EQ wasn't a huge hit, because of death penalties, hell levels, corpse runs, and other time sinks, it was successful in spite of them.<br />
<br />
Now, all of those things are fine in <b>moderation</b>, but EQ pushed them to the extreme, and any developer that thinks they can claim decent market share by reintroducing those type of &quot;features&quot; is on fucking crack.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
