</div>
<br />
Death penalities are needed. Any person who thinks the gameworld will feel the same without them are on fucking crack.<br />
<br />
Hell levels were a bug in the code and fixed. They were never intended. They will not be in Vanguard.<br />
<br />
Corpse Runs were good, added to community, and adds to the death penalty factor. I see no problem with them.<br />
<br />
Just because the game is not doing it like WoW by making everything streamlined without rubbing anything the wrong way (until you have equipment good enough where repair costs will sting. Yet that is only a factor on raids, never in the average run about the world), will not make it a failure. Hell, for me, not having the above things makes it a failure.<br />
<br />
Would a carboncopy of EQ be successful, no. But is Vanguard a carboncopy no. And I am not even remotely going to try and restate all those points. If people still believe VG = EQ, then they have smoked too much crack and are beyond redemption to come back to reality. Their mindset is already set in stone, and there is no point in even arguing with it.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
