<br />
Corpse Runs were good, added to community, and adds to the death penalty factor. I see no problem with them.<br />
<br />
Just because the game is not doing it like WoW by making everything streamlined without rubbing anything the wrong way (until you have equipment good enough where repair costs will sting. Yet that is only a factor on raids, never in the average run about the world), will not make it a failure. Hell, for me, not having the above things makes it a failure.<br /></div>
			
